**Class that compares the variable to another string and returns the result:**
```java
public class Compare {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        String compareString = "Hello";
        boolean isSame = variable.equals(compareString);
        System.out.println("Are they the same? " + isSame);
    }
}
```

---

**Erroneous Code (for reference):**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable;
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

**Errors in the code:**
1. `variable` is declared but not initialized.
2. `System.out.println(variable)` will throw a `NullPointerException` because the variable is not assigned a value.

**Corrected Version:**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

---

All classes manage and manipulate the same original variable `variable`, and the code is corrected to avoid the `NullPointerException`.
